# what/ — Knowledge Layer (Agent Reference)

## Purpose

`what/` holds knowledge objects — the **WHAT** of **{{project_name}}**. Context library, decisions, reference material, and domain-specific entities.

## Subdirectories

| Folder | Purpose | Status |
|--------|---------|--------|
| `context/` | Agent context library — synthesized knowledge for domain work | Required |
| `decisions/` | Architecture Decision Records — significant decisions and rationale | Recommended |

Add project-specific subdirectories as needed (e.g., `datasets/`, `experiments/`, `services/`).

## Working Rules

- All files follow `type_descriptive_name.md` (underscores only, never hyphens)
- Context files carry `token_estimate` in frontmatter for budget planning
- Each entry describes and links to objects — avoid duplicating source material

## Load/Skip Decision

**Load when**: Orienting on knowledge objects or deciding which subdirectory to work in.
**Skip when**: Already know the target subdirectory — go directly to its AGENTS.md.

